!! Location Registry

Locations are tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/file-upload/location` with `type: application/json`. JSON fields:

|!Field |!Type |!Description |
|`name` |string |Unique location name (used in widget `location` attribute and upload API) |
|`uriPrefix` |string |URI path prefix (e.g. `/files/`, `/project-assets/`) |
|`writable` |boolean |Whether upload/delete/rename operations are allowed |
|`basePath` |string |Filesystem path relative to wiki root |
|`provider` |string |Optional: `"scattered-binaries"` if auto-registered by that plugin |
|`subFolder` |string |Optional: subfolder within matched dirs (scattered-binaries only) |

!! Artifact Fields Convention

Derived data linked to a parent file tiddler. Used by cascade delete/rename.

|!Field |!Value |!Description |
|`_artifact_source` |parent tiddler title |Back-reference for cascade operations |
|`_artifact_type` |`thumbnail` / `extraction` / `extraction-image` / `summary` |Type classification |

!! URI Resolver (server-side library)

`require("$:/plugins/rimir/file-upload/uri-resolver")`

|!Method |!Description |
|`resolve(uri)` |Maps canonical URI to absolute filesystem path |
|`resolveSecure(uri)` |Resolves + verifies no path traversal. Returns `{filePath, location}` or null |
|`getLocation(uri)` |Returns location config object for a URI, or null |
|`isWritable(uri)` |Returns boolean |
|`allLocations()` |Returns all registered location configs |
|`buildUri(locationName, relativePath)` |Constructs a canonical URI |
|`invalidate()` |Clears location cache (call after changing location tiddlers at runtime) |

!! Widget: `<$file-dropzone>`

|!Attribute |!Description |
|`actions` |Action string executed on upload completion |
|`location` |Target location name (default: `"files"`). Must be writable. |
|`subfolder` |Optional subfolder override (bypasses built-in routing) |
|`prop-*` |Extra fields passed through as action variables |

Action variables available in `actions`:

|!Variable |!Description |
|`<<data>>` |Raw JSON response body |
|`<<type>>` |MIME type of uploaded file |
|`<<filename>>` |Original filename |
|`<<content-hash>>` |Content hash (8-char hex) |
|`<<canonical-uri>>` |Canonical URI of the uploaded file (e.g. `/files/images/photo.jpg`) |
|`<<generated-uri>>` |Thumbnail URI if processor ran, empty otherwise |
|`<<location>>` |Target location name |

!! Server routes

!!! POST /api/file-upload

|!Request field |!Description |
|`filename` |Original filename |
|`type` |MIME type |
|`content` |Base64-encoded file content |
|`targetPath` |Relative path within the target location |
|`location` |Target location name (default: `"files"`) |

|!Status |!Meaning |
|200 |Success — returns `{canonicalUri, filename, location, generatedUri?, exif?}` |
|400 |Missing fields, invalid JSON, or unknown location |
|403 |Path traversal detected or location is read-only |
|413 |Upload too large (>50MB JSON) |
|415 |MIME type not in whitelist |

!!! POST /api/file-rename

|!Request field |!Description |
|`oldUri` |Current canonical URI |
|`newUri` |Desired canonical URI |

|!Status |!Meaning |
|200 |Success — returns `{newCanonicalUri}` |
|403 |Location is read-only or path traversal |
|404 |Source file not found |
|409 |Target file already exists |

!!! POST /api/file-delete

|!Request field |!Description |
|`uri` |Canonical URI to delete |

|!Status |!Meaning |
|200 |Success — returns `{deleted: true}` |
|403 |Location is read-only or path traversal |
|404 |File not found |

!! Config tiddlers

|!Tiddler |!Default |!Description |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/media-types` |JSON array |Allowed MIME types for upload |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/thumb-images` |`no` |Enable image thumbnail generation |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/thumb-pdfs` |`no` |Enable PDF thumbnail generation |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/thumb-resolution` |`200` |Thumbnail max dimension |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/thumb-rendering` |`no` |Show thumbnails by default in view mode |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/global-dedup` |`no` |Global content-hash deduplication |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/exif-extraction` |`yes` |Extract EXIF metadata from uploaded images (requires ImageMagick) |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/exif-mapping` |JSON object |Global EXIF-to-field mapping: `{"ExifTag": "tiddler-field"}` |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/exif-mapping/<loc>` |JSON object |Per-location override (replaces global mapping for that location) |

!! EXIF extraction

When enabled, EXIF metadata is extracted from uploaded images via `magick.exe identify` and auto-applied as tiddler fields based on the field mapping config.

Available EXIF tags: `DateTimeOriginal`, `Make`, `Model`, `ExifImageWidth`, `ExifImageHeight`, `GPSLatitudeDecimal`, `GPSLongitudeDecimal`, `Orientation`, `ExposureTime`, `FNumber`, `ISO`, `FocalLength`, `LensModel`.

Default mapping produces fields: `exif-date`, `exif-make`, `exif-model`, `exif-width`, `exif-height`, `exif-gps-lat`, `exif-gps-lon`, `exif-orientation`, `exif-exposure`, `exif-fnumber`, `exif-iso`, `exif-focal-length`, `exif-lens`.

Per-location overrides: create `$:/config/rimir/file-upload/exif-mapping/<location-name>` with a JSON object to use different field names for a specific location.

